<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 7:50
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='459000' id='t-459000'>The next video is not done by us.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='461000' id='t-461000'>This is CBS Sunday Morning that aired about two weeks ago.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='465000' id='t-465000'>Scott Adams ran into us</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='467000' id='t-467000'>and asked us if we wouldn't help to design</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='469000' id='t-469000'>the ultimate cubicle for Dilbert,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='471000' id='t-471000'>which sounded like a fun thing and so we couldn't pass it up.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='475000' id='t-475000'>He's always been interested in technology in the future.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:09
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='478000' id='t-478000'>(Video: Scott Adams: I realized that at some point I might be</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='480000' id='t-480000'>the world's expert on what's wrong with cubicles.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='483000' id='t-483000'>So we thought, well, wouldn't it be fun to get together</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='485000' id='t-485000'>with some of the smartest design guys in the world</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='487000' id='t-487000'>and try to figure out if we could make the cubicle better?</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:21
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='490000' id='t-490000'>Narrator: Though they work in a wide-open office space</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='493000' id='t-493000'>spectacularly set under San Francisco's Oakland Bay Bridge,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='498000' id='t-498000'>the team built their own little cubicles</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='500000' id='t-500000'>to fully experience the problems.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:34
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='503000' id='t-503000'>Woman: A one-way mirror. I can look out; you can look at yourself.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:37
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='506000' id='t-506000'>Narrator: They took pictures.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:38
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='507000' id='t-507000'>Woman: You feel so trapped, when someone kind of leans over</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='510000' id='t-510000'>and you're sort of held captive there for a minute.</span>
</span>
